  "lore": "A Legion Delegatus is a mid-ranking Legion officer, such as a centurion, tasked with a specific mission by a Legion’s High Command and formally deputised to act in all matters with the full weight of their commander’s authority. As such, they can mobilise the Legion’s resources to the full, deploy its assets and, if performing a mission of vital strategic worth, assemble a strike force of chosen warriors.",
